!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

scope /skəʊp/

1. N-UNCOUNT If there is scope for a particular kind of behaviour or activity, people have the opportunity to behave in this way or do that activity. 机会 

例： He believed in giving his staff scope for initiative. 他赞成给他的员工主动的机会。 

2. N-SING The scope of an activity, topic, or piece of work is the whole area which it deals with or includes. 范围 

例： Mr. Dobson promised to widen the organization's scope of activity. 多布森先生答应扩大该组织的活动范围。

</div>

